  "market_context": "Price in a downtrend reversed after breaking and closing above a major swing high at 1.09700, confirming a Change of Character. The analyst examined entry options within the discount zone formed by HTF and LTF order blocks.",
  "key_observation": "Price respected the higher timeframe order block (HTF OB) but missed the extreme lower timeframe order block (Extreme LTF OB), illustrating that excessive refinement reduces probability; FVGs on LTF are often more reliably respected than extreme LTF OBs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a downtrend ending with a Break of Structure (BOS) and subsequent Change of Character (CHoCH) above the major high at 1.09700 on the daily chart.",
    "Step 2: Located the discount zone containing both a higher timeframe order block (HTF OB) and an extreme lower timeframe order block (Extreme LTF OB).",
    "Step 3: Noted that entering at the HTF OB yields a large stop loss and poor risk-reward, while entering at the Extreme LTF OB is unrealistic due to infrequent deep retracements.",
    "Step 4: Proposed using the Fair Value Gap (FVG) below the HTF OB as a higher-probability entry zone on the lower timeframe, with stop loss below the Extreme LTF OB.",
    "Step 5: Warned that placing stop loss too tight (just below FVG) risks being stopped out by the influence of the Extreme LTF OB."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Higher timeframe order blocks are more reliably respected than extreme lower timeframe ones; fair value gaps on lower timeframes often provide better entry precision without sacrificing probability, but stop placement must account for deeper liquidity zones.",
